data.consensus_text: The dam is reported to have added 10' to the level of the original lakes.

5 ft. (See notes card) east of Hasting's Pt. (1 ft. wide, 1 in. deep); west of Trail's End Trail (2 ft. wide, 2 in. deep); east side of lake, from private lake, with water gage at culvert (3 ft. wide, 3 in. deep); south shore near east side (5 ft. wide, 4 in. deep); into Robbin's Bay (6 ft. wide, 3 in. deep, near road bridge).
40ft. wide with an ave. depth of 4ft.
1 ft Dam so constructed that it probably does not stop fish movement. Dam constructed about 5 feet high and made so that boards can control water level for about one foot in height.
